See https://www.imf.org/external/terms.htm and in particular:

When Data is distributed or reproduced, it must appear accurately and 
attributed to the IMF as the source, e.g. “Source: International Monetary 
Fund.”. This source attribution requirement is attached to any use of IMF Data, 
whether obtained directly from the IMF or from a User. Users who make IMF Data 
available to other users through any type of distribution or download 
environment agree to take reasonable efforts to communicate and promote 
compliance by their End Users with these terms. 
